### Test Multi-Tenant Data Isolation

@tenant1Id = aaaaaaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaaaaaaaaaa
@tenant2Id = bbbbbbbb-bbbb-bbbb-bbbb-bbbbbbbbbbbb

### Test 1a: Create user for Tenant 1
POST http://localhost:5036/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json
X-Tenant-Id: {{tenant1Id}}

{
  "email": "john@tenant1.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe"
}

###

### Test 1b: Get all users for Tenant 1 (should see John)
GET http://localhost:5036/api/v1/users
X-Tenant-Id: {{tenant1Id}}

###

### Test 2a: Create user for Tenant 2
POST http://localhost:5036/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json
X-Tenant-Id: {{tenant2Id}}

{
  "email": "jane@tenant2.com",
  "password": "password456",
  "firstName": "Jane",
  "lastName": "Smith"
}

###

### Test 2b: Get all users for Tenant 2 (should see Jane only, NOT John)
GET http://localhost:5036/api/v1/users
X-Tenant-Id: {{tenant2Id}}

###

### Test 3: Tenant 1 tries to access their users again (should still only see John)
GET http://localhost:5036/api/v1/users
X-Tenant-Id: {{tenant1Id}}

###

### Test 4: Try to create duplicate email within same tenant (should fail)
POST http://localhost:5036/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json
X-Tenant-Id: {{tenant1Id}}

{
  "email": "john@tenant1.com",
  "password": "differentpassword",
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Another"
}

###

### Test 5: Create same email in different tenant (should succeed - multi-tenant isolation)
POST http://localhost:5036/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json
X-Tenant-Id: {{tenant2Id}}

{
  "email": "john@tenant1.com",
  "password": "password789",
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "TwoTenant"
}
